parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to total loss, and can also pose a risk to the driver's safety.
symptoms: Sudden fire in the engine compartment
melted air filter box and assembly
melted windshield washer bottle
damaged wiring harness
smoke filling the interior of the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power suddenly, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls without warning
vehicle stalls intermittently
dealer unable to determine cause.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, from minor inconvenience to safety risks, and can also lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: Headlights and dashboard indication lights cut off
vehicle unable to start
instrument panel shorts out
failure of all gauges
ignition key failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbag to Deploy in Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injury or even death, as the driver and passengers are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in a collision
despite meeting the necessary criteria for deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper airbag deployment can cause serious injury or death, as the airbag may not provide the necessary protection or may even cause harm to the driver or passengers.
symptoms: The airbag deploys in a collision
but does so in a manner that is not intended
such as deploying too aggressively or at the wrong time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can lead to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and loss of control, potentially resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the ABS and hydraulic lights appear on the dashboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal feels hard
the brake system fails intermittently
the brake system fails completely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can lead to loss of control, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents, potentially resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light appears on the dashboard
the brake pedal feels hard
the brake system fails intermittently
the brake system fails completely
the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the vehicle is unable to maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the cooling system can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The radiator hoses are damaged or leaking
the coolant level is low
the engine temperature gauge is in the red zone
the engine is overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause engine damage, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents due to reduced lubrication.
symptoms: The oil pan gasket is leaking
oil is dripping from the engine
the oil level is low
the engine is making unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the accessory belts can cause engine damage, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents due to reduced engine performance.
symptoms: The belts are cracked or damaged
the belts are making unusual noises
the engine is overheating
the power steering or alternator is not functioning.
